    <text>
        <body><div type="bibliography">
                
                <p><bibl><ptr target="#mohamed-jmr-cdl2007"/>, p. 44, n. <citedRange>10</citedRange></bibl>, whence 
                    <bibl><ptr target="#SEG"/>, <citedRange>57.2009</citedRange></bibl>;
                    <bibl><ptr target="#IGCyr"/> <citedRange>109100</citedRange></bibl>.</p>
            </div><div type="edition" xml:lang="grc" xml:space="preserve">
                
                <ab>
                    <lb n="1"/><gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/><orig>σατ</orig><gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/>
                </ab></div><div type="apparatus" xml:space="preserve">
            
                <p/>
               </div><div type="translation" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="fr">
            <p>Intraduisible.</p>
         </div><div type="translation" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="en">
            <p>Not usefully translatable.</p>
         </div><div type="translation" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="it">
            <p>Intraducibile.</p>
         </div><div type="translation" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="ar">
            <p>غير قابل للترجمة بشكل جيد</p>
         </div><div type="commentary">
                
                <p>The placement of the shallow curve on upper side seems to show that not much is lost at right end, so that we might have the end of an
                artist's signature <foreign xml:lang="grc">ἠργάσ(σ)ατο</foreign> like that of <ref type="inscription" source="#IGCyr2">IGCyr019000</ref>. But this should not be pushed
                too far ahead because of the very lacunar condition of the fragment.</p>
                <p/>
            </div></body>
